---
import Layout from "$layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Fireplace Finishes" description="[copy needed]">

	<section class="MaxWidthSmall">
		<h1>Exclusive Custom Finishes</h1>
		<p>Every fireplace deserves a finish that complements your unique vision. That's why we offer two signature finishes, each meticulously applied by hand to enhance the natural beauty and texture of cast iron.</p>
		<figure class="FeatureSet">
			<img src="#" alt="" />
			<figcaption>
				<h2>Blackened Bronze</h2>
				<p>Rich, sophisticated, and timelessly elegant. Our Blackened Bronze finish combines deep charcoal tones with subtle bronze undertones that catch and reflect light beautifully. This finish adds depth and dimension to ornate detailing, making every curve and pattern stand out with quiet drama.</p>
				<p>Perfect for creating contrast in lighter rooms or adding refined gravitas to period interiors. The darkened patina evokes the authenticity of antique metalwork while remaining perfectly suited to contemporary spaces seeking a touch of heritage character.</p>
			</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<figure class="FeatureSet">
			<img src="#" alt="" />
			<figcaption>
				<h2>Iron Lustre</h2>
				<p>Celebrating cast iron in its most honest form. Iron Lustre is a soft, matte finish that honors the raw beauty of the metal itself. With gentle grey tones and a naturally weathered appearance, this finish brings an organic, understated elegance to any room.</p>
				<p>Ideal for those who appreciate industrial aesthetics, Scandinavian simplicity, or the quiet sophistication of natural materials. Iron Lustre works beautifully in both minimalist modern spaces and traditional settings where subtle texture speaks louder than shine.</p>
			</figcaption>
		</figure>
		<!-- <hr> -->
		<h2>Hand-Applied Craftsmanship</h2>
		<p>Each finish is carefully applied and treated to protect against wear while maintaining the tactile quality of genuine cast iron. These aren't mass-produced coatings—they're artisan finishes designed to age gracefully and develop character over time.</p>
	</section>

</Layout>